Generate random censored data

Generate random censored data

generate_censored_data(N, rho, L_prob, direction = c(-1), adj = FALSE,
  adj_sigma = NULL)

Arguments

N

number of rows
rho

true correlation
L_prob

percentage of data to censor
direction

types of censoring to include; acceptable values are -1 (left), 1 (right), 2 (interval) or any combination
adj

whether to adjust values by a normally distributed variable
adj_sigma

if adj is true, this specifies the standard deviation of the adjustment variable

Value

data frame

Details

When multiple types of censoring are requested, the function evenly splits the censored values across all the types. Interval censoring is always done around the center of the distribution.

Examples


# Generate 100 x and y values with a 0.5 correlation and 50% left-censored
generate_censored_data(100, rho = 0.5, L_prob = 0.5, direction = -1)
